Drop the Qt::CorePrivate dependency from base for the vendored Qt 6 build.

qBittorrent 4.6.4+ reads QT_FEATURE_icu from the private Qt header
<QtCore/private/qtcore-config_p.h> in src/base/utils/compare.h and links the
Qt::CorePrivate CMake target solely to decide whether QCollator's ICU-backed
natural sort is available (otherwise it falls back to a portable comparator).

brrewery's vendored, minimal Qt 6 build (-no-gui -no-widgets) does not expose
the Qt::CorePrivate CMake target, so the qbittorrent-nox configure step fails
at generate time with:

  CMake Error at src/base/CMakeLists.txt:195 (target_link_libraries):
    Target "qbt_base" links to:
      Qt::CorePrivate
    but the target was not found.

brrewery always builds Qt with ICU (libicu-dev is a build dependency, see
tasks/dependencies.yml), so QT_FEATURE_icu would be 1 anyway. Enable QCollator
unconditionally, drop the private header include, and remove the now-unused
Qt::CorePrivate link. This preserves the ICU-backed natural sort upstream
intends on this configuration while removing the private dependency.

--- a/src/base/utils/compare.h
+++ b/src/base/utils/compare.h
@@ -31,17 +31,14 @@
 #include <Qt>
 #include <QtGlobal>
 
-// for QT_FEATURE_xxx, see: https://wiki.qt.io/Qt5_Build_System#How_to
-#include <QtCore/private/qtcore-config_p.h>
-
-// macOS and Windows support 'case sensitivity' and 'numeric mode' natively
-// https://github.com/qt/qtbase/blob/6.0/src/corelib/CMakeLists.txt#L777-L793
-// https://github.com/qt/qtbase/blob/6.0/src/corelib/text/qcollator_macx.cpp#L74-L77
-// https://github.com/qt/qtbase/blob/6.0/src/corelib/text/qcollator_win.cpp#L72-L78
-#if ((QT_FEATURE_icu == 1) || defined(Q_OS_MACOS) || defined(Q_OS_WIN))
+// brrewery: upstream reads QT_FEATURE_icu from <QtCore/private/qtcore-config_p.h>
+// and links Qt::CorePrivate only to choose QCollator's ICU-backed natural sort.
+// The vendored minimal Qt build does not expose the Qt::CorePrivate CMake target,
+// so configure fails. brrewery always builds Qt with ICU (libicu-dev is a build
+// dependency), so enable QCollator unconditionally and drop the private include.
+// The matching CMakeLists hunk removes the Qt::CorePrivate link.
 #define QBT_USE_QCOLLATOR
 #include <QCollator>
-#endif
 
 class QString;
 
--- a/src/base/CMakeLists.txt
+++ b/src/base/CMakeLists.txt
@@ -200,7 +200,6 @@
     PUBLIC
         LibtorrentRasterbar::torrent-rasterbar
         Qt::Core
-        Qt::CorePrivate
         Qt::Network
         Qt::Sql
         Qt::Xml
